    {
        "content": "<p>Would be nice, if it was pinned against a specific git commit instead of <code>#HEAD</code>, then can have a static hash.</p>\n<p>I prefer reproduce-ability, and manually bumping, over automated bleeding edge and the occasional breakage.</p>\n<p>Which is a good point, i'll add static commit id for the template also...</p>\n<p>And i can override with my own zon file with a static commit id for roc.</p>",
        "id": 561100181,
        "sender_full_name": "Scott Campbell",
        "timestamp": 1764579695
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Once we have a numbered release I would pin to that, but for now we are updating things quite frequently... though any actual changes to the builtins are rare.</p>\n<p>In theory we could have a totally separate library for the RocStr/RocList etc we are using in the platform, but for now it's easy just to treat the roc repository as a library and borrow our builtin module directly.</p>",
        "id": 561101356,
        "sender_full_name": "Luke Boswell",
        "timestamp": 1764580020
